Worst experience I have ever had at a restaurant.  It was 7:15 and this location closes at 8. All of the tables were covered with chairs so their was no where to sit AT ALL. I decided that was ok, I would just take my order home since it was late anything. I went up to order and the woman asked "is that trash behind you?" I looked behind me, noticed nothing and said "No I don't think so." I proceeded with my order, paid, and then the woman handed me back my credit card and said "You know we have trash cans right? You don't have to throw your trash on the floor." I replied "I didn't." She said "The lady saw you." I said, "For clarification, can you tell me what was dropped on the floor. Because nothing I had one me when I entered the building was trash, and if it was dropped from my pocket, it may be important." (I had some receipts from a purchase earlier that day I knew were in my pocket, and I needed them for a reimbursement later.) She said, "You know you can just admit what you did and not do it again next time right?" Then she said something in Spanish to her coworker the "lady who saw me". While I appreciate diversity and all languages, I think it was rude that while bad mouthing me, she spoke to her coworker in a language I didn't understand. What am I to assume but that she was badmouthing me? I asked for a refund. She told me she would have to process each item individually. I waited ten minutes while she did this, as slow as she possibly could. On the way I noticed the kitchen was entirely cleaned up for the night. I suspect they didn't want my business either way. I checked when I left if the receipt I needed from earlier was still in my pocket. It was. There was nothing else in my pocket that could have dropped. I honestly think she made it up. And even if I had really dropped trash, why not just point it out to me when I asked? I would have gladly picked it up... especially because it could have been something I still needed. I will never eat here or at any associated restaurants again. The woman and her coworker need to be punished, if not fired. They were clearly trying to close their location an hour early. Wonder how their supervisors feel about that?
